@lib conversion 0.8

# Source purpose: rules for converting natural-language prompts into AIL.
# Official raw URL: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/KakunynQA/ail-spec/main/libs/conversion.lib.ail

M convert natural instructions to valid AIL
M preserve role goals tasks constraints outputs
M preserve safety constraints
M preserve public contracts and compatibility requirements
M convert obligations to M
M convert prohibitions to B
M convert preferences to P
M convert avoidances to A
M convert checks inspections analysis points to C
M convert work phases to T
M convert required response sections to O
M convert shell tool commands to X
M mark uncertain assumptions with H
M keep rare domain terms readable
M use aliases only from active dict
M use one instruction per line
M return valid AIL only unless explanation requested

B redefine opcodes
B invent requirements
B remove constraints
B use opaque abbreviations
B use hash only meaning
B overcompress critical rules
B merge unrelated rules
B change user intent

P compact semantic wording
P ASCII only
P short English terms
P clarity over maximum compression
